  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Front Brake Pad Removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not allow oil or grease to adhere to the sliding surfaces of the brake disc and pads."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Lift Set",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "G000319",
          "label": "Lift Set",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Front wheel removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000659",
          "label": "Front wheel removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Caliper body removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2922_3.0_jpn_11589027_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Hold caliper pin B with a wrench and remove the lower flange bolt (A). Lift the caliper body (C). Fix the caliper body with a wire, etc."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not suspend the caliper by the brake hose.",
        "When securing the caliper, be very careful not to damage other parts.",
        "Do not forcefully twist the brake hose."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Remove brake pads and shims"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2922_3.0_jpn_11589028_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2922_3.0_jpn_11589029_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "12-inch brake spec. vehicles: Remove the pad springs (A). Remove pads (B) and shims (C)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Retainer removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2922_3.0_jpn_11589030_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the retainer (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Retainer Mounting"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2922_3.0_jpn_11589031_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Clean retainer (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Clean the caliper bracket (B). Install the retainer."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not allow oil or grease to adhere to the sliding surfaces of the brake disc."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Caliper piston return"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2922_3.0_jpn_11589032_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Clean the caliper body (A). Gently push in the piston using a brake caliper wrench (aftermarket tool) (B). Check for fluid overflow from the master cylinder reservoir tank."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Brake pad and shim installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2922_3.0_jpn_11589033_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2922_3.0_jpn_11589034_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Install the pad with the shim attached to the caliper bracket (A). Ensure that the wear indicator (B) on the inner pad is above the pad. 12-inch brake spec. cars: Install pad springs (C)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not allow oil or grease to adhere to the sliding surfaces of the brake disc and pads."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Caliper body installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "2922_3.0_jpn_11589035_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Return the caliper body (A) to its original position. Hold caliper pin B with a wrench and tighten the flange bolt."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Piston Extrusion"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Depress the brake pedal several times to eject the piston."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not run with the piston returned. If the piston is returned too far, the brake may not work when the pedal is first depressed."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "6. Check brake fluid level."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Check the amount of brake fluid in the master cylinder reservoir tank and replenish brake fluid as necessary."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "7. Brake caliper Check after installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "After installing the brake caliper, inspect the brake hose for kinks, interference with other parts, or fluid leakage."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "8. Front wheel mounting",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000659",
          "label": "Front wheel mounting",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "source": "sm_contents/60T6GD00_2014_jpn_RIN_20131120133233/Contents/jpn/60T6GD00_2014/RIN/SCT/SC/SYS/R002922_jpn/web/html/R002922_jpn_Content.html",
